In Huntsville, AL a tornado slammed into a shopping district, a residential area, and a school  Wednesday, killing at least 15 people.
305 people were injured and about 500 displaced.
People  are still trapped in vehicles, apartment complexes, and shopping areas.
The rubble is 10 to 14  feet deep and rescuers are hampered by darkness and plunging temperatures.
Doctors were  having difficulty reaching the Humana Hospital because of blocked roads.
At least three other tornadoes have been reported across Alabama.
In Georgia, a tornado struck  southeast of Palmetto, and a pair of tornadoes struck in Henderson County, NC. 
